<table align="center" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0" ><tr ><td valign="top" width="650" ><div class="mktEditable" id="left-column" ><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="10" width="630">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td height="229" align="left" valign="top">
<div align="left"><img src="http://pages3.honeywell.com/rs/honeywell3/images/DS_Aircraft650x150.jpg" alt="" width="650" height="150" /></div>
<div align="left">
<p><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">In an ongoing effort to reduce order processing holds and improve your customer order turnaround times, Honeywell Aerospace is re-communicating our policy for processing repair orders.    &nbsp;While we have always maintained a 10-day Return As Is (RAI) policy, Honeywell will begin strictly enforcing the policy starting on June 30, 2014.    The key elements of the policy as are as follows:</span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">A funded Purchase Order (P.O.) based on either an established Contract price, or if not under a Long Term Contract, then a Universal Flat Rate (UFR) price, will need to be submitted at time of order for all   incoming units.<br />&nbsp; </span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">For parts where no Contracted price or Universal Flat Rate (UFR) pricing is available, a funded Purchase Order (PO) should be submitted with the published Test, Teardown, Evaluation (TTE) fee.    After the unit is evaluated, Honeywell will provide a notification with the Time and Material price.<br />&nbsp; </span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">If units are received without a funded Purchase Order, customers will be contacted and asked to submit the properly funded P.O.    immediately.</span> 
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Orders will be   placed  on an internal hold for 10 days while awaiting the P.O.&nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Customers will receive 1    additional follow-up email/phone call.    &nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">If no funded P.O.    is received in 10 days, per the standard Honeywell RAI&nbsp;policy, the unit will be Returned As Is to the customer without any testing&nbsp;or evaluation performed.&nbsp;</span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">No fees will be invoiced.</span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">(It should be noted that in cases when Warranty coverage is requested, the standard adjudication will take place. For instance, where Warranty is denied, customers will be notified to submit a funded-P.O. to allow repair work to continue and the RAI process will apply accordingly.)</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">As part of the Honeywell commitment to our customers, we will be instituting the following internal improvements: </span></p>
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">More robust internal procedures for handling escalated items; such as errors or disputes, to ensure timely resolution</span> 
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Please note that customer escalations must be made back to Honeywell within the 10 day time frame to avoid return of product<br /><br /></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Standardized procedures for submittal of all quote approvals, funded P.O.'s and/or information requests for all Honeywell Aerospace sites:</span> 
<ul>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Quotes approvals and communications online at </span><a style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;" href="http://www.myaerospace.com/">www.myaerospace.com</a></li>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Direct response to original email received from </span><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><a title="D&amp;SRepairs@Honeywell.com" href="mailto:D&amp;SRepairs@Honeywell.com">D&amp;Srepairs@honeywell.com</a></span></span></li>
<li><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Contact Honeywell directly at&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva;"><span style="font-size: 14px;"><a title="AeroR&amp;OD&amp;S@Honeywell.com" href="mailto:AeroR&amp;OD&amp;S@Honeywell.com">AeroR&amp;OD&amp;S@Honeywell.com</a></span></span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Honeywell&rsquo;s Universal Flat Rate repair pricing and TT&amp;E pricing is available on the Honeywell web portal <a href="http://www.myaerospace.com/">www.myaerospace.com</a>.    &nbsp;You may also request a complete current UFR price list from your Customer Business Manager.</span><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Sincerely,</span></p>
<p><span style="font-family: verdana, geneva; font-size: 14px;">Honeywell Defense and Space&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
